Text:
You're fine on your own, huh? Yeah...I can tell
you're strong.

(The cat's face suddenly pops into my head. Is this
therianthrope trying to make a fool of me too?)

You're way different than me. I'm weak...
Couldn't protect the others.

(But...I don't get the impression that she's trying
to make fun of me.)

(If anything it kinda feels more like she's making
fun of herself...

So what about you? Where's your pack? Are you holed
up in this cave because you're an outcast?

An outcast... Guess you could say that.
I got separated from my pack.
They're not in this world anymore. They're dead...
Dead? From fighting over territory?

No, it was a bear. An incredibly fierce one lives
nearby. He wiped out our village all by himself—
I see...

(You hear stories like that a lot. If you're weak,
you die. That's how our world works.)

(Sometimes we therianthropes fight for territory among
ourselves, and sometimes we fight strong animals...)

(The weak submit to the strong. That's our law. 
And she lost to the bear, it was as simple as that.)

Dammit, I'll show him! Once this wound heals,
I'll build a new pack!
Then I'll kill that bear and avenge the others!
You're gonna fight?

Of course I am! I can't let him get away with killin'
my packmates! I'll fight for as long as I live!
Packmates...

...Anyway, now is the time for me to rest. You want
somethin’ to eat? All I got are nuts and herbs, though.
I'm fine. I just ate something I caught.
Okay...

It's gonna be pourin’ today, so stay here tonight. 
It should clear up by tomorrow.
...Okay, I will.

(Sure, I've bumped into someone kinda weird, but I'll
be outta this cave as soon as the rain lets up...)
I can't sleep, even after closing my eyes...

"Of course I am! I can't let him get away with killin'
my packmates! I'll fight for as long as I live!"
(A word she said bothered me, it won't let me sleep.)
(Packmates...)

(Saying it conjures up images of Boss...and Lady
Alpha again.)
(Why am I thinking of them all now?)
(I'm strong. I'll be fine all by myself.)
(But then why...)

(Thinking about everyone all the way back at
the Shadow Garden...)
(...makes my chest get all tight and sharp inside...)
(It's a strange feeling.)

(Why is that pack stuck in my mind? I've already left
them behind, after all...)
...Hey, wake up.

It's him... The monster of a bear that slaughtered
my pack is close.

(The bear is already inside the cave. How did it get
so close without me noticing?)

(I was too caught up thinking about packmates. I need
to pay attention.)

He must've followed the scent of my blood...
I thought that all this rain would cover it up.
...Did you bring anything from your village?

Anything? No, all I brought was this bag my packmate
used.

She glances over at a hip pouch full of nuts and
medicinal herbs laying on the floor of the cave.

That's why he's here. Bears are really vindictive, 
so if you steal something from 'em, they always
come to reclaim what's theirs.

But this was my packmate's— Actually, no, a bear
wouldn't understand that.
He's...getting closer!
